<P>The computer company you work for is introducing a brand new computer =
line=20
and is developing a new Unix-like operating system to be introduced =
along with=20
the new computer. Your assignment is to write the formatter for the =
<TT>ls</TT>=20
function.=20
<P>
<P>Your program will eventually read input from a pipe (although for now =
your=20
program will read from the input file). Input to your program will =
consist of a=20
list of (<I>F</I>) filenames that you will sort (ascending based on the =
ASCII=20
character values) and format into (<I>C</I>) columns based on the length =

(<I>L</I>) of the longest filename. Filenames will be between 1 and 60=20
(inclusive) characters in length and will be formatted into =
left-justified=20
columns. The rightmost column will be the width of the longest filename =
and all=20
other columns will be the width of the longest filename plus 2. There =
will be as=20
many columns as will fit in 60 characters. Your program should use as =
few rows=20
(<I>R</I>) as possible with rows being filled to capacity from left to =
right.=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001001000000000000000>Input</A></FONT></H2>
<P>The input file will contain an indefinite number of lists of =
filenames. Each=20
list will begin with a line containing a single integer ( <IMG=20
alt=3Dtex2html_wrap_inline41 align=3Dmiddle=20
src=3D"file:///C:/Users/WU%20YONGHUI/AppData/Local/Temp/Rar$EX00.449/400i=
mg1.gif"=20
width=3D95 height=3D26> ). There will then be <I>N</I> lines each =
containing one=20
left-justified filename and the entire line's contents (between 1 and 60 =

characters) are considered to be part of the filename. Allowable =
characters are=20
alphanumeric (<TT>a</TT> to <TT>z</TT>, <TT>A</TT> to <TT>Z</TT>, and =
<TT>0</TT>=20
to <TT>9</TT>) and from the following set <CODE>{ ._- }</CODE> (not =
including=20
the curly braces). There will be no illegal characters in any of the =
filenames=20
and no line will be completely empty.=20
<P>Immediately following the last filename will be the <I>N</I> for the =
next set=20
or the end of file. You should read and format all sets in the input =
file.=20
<P>
<H2><FONT color=3D#0070e8><A=20
name=3DSECTION0001002000000000000000>Output</A></FONT></H2>
<P>For each set of filenames you should print a line of exactly 60 =
dashes=20
(<TT>-</TT>) followed by the formatted columns of filenames. The sorted=20
filenames 1 to <I>R</I> will be listed down column 1; filenames =
<I>R</I>+1 to=20
2<I>R</I> listed down column 2; etc.=20
<P>
